		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I will agree with byuu about the sound. There's enough documentation about the CGRAM, and the basics of how all the backgrounds work, but the sound is some weird mystery land. <br />Even if you are a programmer and musician, you have to use trackers with the existing tools, which I assume for many non nerds is pretty weird territory.<br />I'm learning the 65816 ASM again and hit a crazy wall with just getting sound to output.<br />I think with a little bit better documentation in a few years there could be some doooope stuff coming from the SNES homebrew world.

		

